Subject: [PATCH AP-02] vmmon: remove bare return; at end of void functions in phystrack.c

Kernel 6.17+ objtool treats an explicit `return;` at the very end of a void
function as dead code after a RET instruction, causing a build failure:

  phystrack.o: error: objtool: PhysTrack_Test()+0x...: unreachable instruction

The fix removes the redundant bare `return;` statements that immediately
precede the closing `}` of void functions. The compiler generates identical
code either way; the only difference is whether objtool finds the return
reachable.

This patch shows the canonical removal for the two affected void functions
in phystrack.c. The script uses a regex (`\s+return;\n(\s*\})`) to find
and remove all such occurrences idempotently.

Applied by: _autopatch_phystrack_bare_returns() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  kernel >= 6.17 or >= 7.x  (KernelVersion.needs_objtool_patches())

---
 vmmon-only/common/phystrack.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/vmmon-only/common/phystrack.c b/vmmon-only/common/phystrack.c
--- a/vmmon-only/common/phystrack.c
+++ b/vmmon-only/common/phystrack.c
@@ -321,7 +321,6 @@ PhysTrack_Test(void)
          printk(KERN_DEBUG "PhysTracker: All tests passed\n");
       }
    }
-   return;
 }
 
 
@@ -365,7 +364,6 @@ PhysTrack_Cleanup(void)
       Hash_Free(physTracker.hash);
       physTracker.hash = NULL;
    }
-   return;
 }
